<item>
            <title>[JDK-8316859] RISC-V: Disable detection of V through HWCAP</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316859</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Some dev boards only support RVV version 0.7, while the OpenJDK only supports RVV version 1.0. These two versions are not compatible with each other. Given the V bit is set through HWCAP on some custom kernels, regardless of the version, it can lead to generating V instructions on boards that don&amp;#39;t support RVV version 1.0 (ex: Sipeed LicheePi or VisionFive 2), leading to a SIGILL.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
That is an acceptable workaround as only Linux Kernel v6.5+ supports V, and that version already support hwprobe anyway</description>
